text:
Although the food is decent and I often patronize this restaurant, I found a feather in my food today.

I'm deeply disappointed and hope they will take this feedback and food safety seriously.

I came here specially to try their Dosai. My conclusion is that it is one of the best Dosai I have had so far (how I assess whether it is to my likely is by going for the plain version the first time). I asked for the Dosai to be more crispy and the stallholder was very kind to agree to immediately. Thanks for being customer oriented. I will definitely come back for other items.

PS: The dosai pairs wonderfully with a cup of Ginger O from the stall beside.

Having tried most Indian vegetarians place nearby Jurong east area, I can confidently say this has to be one of the best and cheapest meals I had. Both in terms of quality and quantity. I’ll definitely come again. Highly recommended.

Morning till night, here’s your place for crispy dosai! Usually eat it with sugar, like how i have my prate, but their accompanying sauces are light and refreshing.
Fairly priced accompanied with friendly staff who patiently runs me through their options.
To erect more tables as currently there are only. 4 to 5 tables to be seated by a group of 10 to 12 pax.
